  "elapsed_s": 9.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We [INAUDIBLE] so [INAUDIBLE] upset-- [INAUDIBLE] to see, we knew then, that was the day that-- that-- they died.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We knew it.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they did it in the night, I guess.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "That's what happened.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Because by the time they brought her in, it was already day time, you know, until they go through all this-- what we went through.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So it means that we knew already.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "That was the last transport from Greece.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And-- and then, my brother went into the orchestra, because he-- he said he was a musician.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They took him.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But the orchestra didn't have-- their orchestra didn't have the same privileges we had.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They made them work half of the day.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they was chosen for-- for instance, every-- every three or four months in-- it-- you know, an order would come from Germany that the people, the girls who had been working in the camp, now they're too sick-- look sick or have things in her-- their body, stains-- you know, things like that.",
      "word_count": 54
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They said that they have to go straight to the gas chambers.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And so-- so what they did, is they-- they used to take them in the camp in the morning, and late in the evening, and they used it all the time that we were all in bed.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And they had them naked.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And they would see what they have, if they have anything wrong with their bodies, or they look-- they are too thin.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Then they choose which ones will go to the gas chamber.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "They already knew, the girls, that there is gas chamber.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Was-- that was the toughest thing.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And one-- the two-- two girls went to the gas chamber were my first cousins, these pictures I showed you.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "They were my first cousins.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
